<p>Kalbi, Bibim-Bop, and Banchan are popular Korean dishes </p>
<br/>
<p>Kalbi is Korean Barbequed Beef Short Ribs.</p>
<p>The short ribs are marinated in soy sauce, brown sugar, sesame oil, garlic, and mirin</p>
<p>and grilled over an open flame or cooked on a cast iron grill.</p>
<br/>
<p>Bibim-Bop, which means "mixed rice", consists of a bowl of rice topped with a variety of vegetables,</p>
<p>korean pepper paste, sunny-side-up egg, and sliced meat.</p>
<br/>
<p>Banchan are side dishes that are served alongside all Korean meals</p>
<br/><br/> 

<h4>Kalbi Recipe</h4>
<p>Ingredients</p>
<p>5 pounds Korean style beef short ribs</p>
<p>1 cup brown sugar, packed</p>
<p>1 cup soy sauce</p>
<p>1/2 cup water</p>
<p>1/4 cup mirin ( rice wine)</p>
<p>1 small onion, peeled and finely grated</p>
<p>1 small Asian pear, peeled and finely grated</p>
<p>4 tablespoons minced garlic</p>
<p>2 tablespoons dark sesame oil</p>
<p>1/4 teaspoon black pepper</p>
<p>2 green onions, thinly sliced (optional)</p>
<h4>Directions</h4>
<p>Mix all ingredients.  Stack the beef ribs into a pan and cover with marinade.  Marinate overnight.</p>
<p>Cook on high heat or grill for 2-3 minutes each side.  Sprinkle with sesame seeds and sliced green onions.</p>
 



